-- Suez’s Degremont Acquires Industrial Water France Unit From BASF
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-05-16T09:57:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-16/suez-s-degremont-acquires-industrial-water-france-unit-from-basf.html
Degremont, the water-treatment
subsidiary of  Suez Environnement (SEV) , acquired  BASF SE (BAS) ’s Industrial
Water Management France SAS business.  Neither BASF nor Suez, Europe’s second-largest water
company, gave terms in their statements. Industrial Water, based
in Lyon with a second production site in La Courneuve, mainly
operates in France, the Benelux countries and Italy, the
companies said yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
